
In terminal:
  sudo mknod /dev/<myDeviceFileName> <c/b> <Major#> <Minor#>
<myDeviceFileName> : Device file name
<c/b> : Character device (c) or Block device (b)
<Major#> : Major number of driver ckeck "/usr/src/linux/Documentation/ide/ide.txt" for fill list of Major numbers being used to prevent clashes.
<Minor#> : Minor numner of device handled by driver.

To check out a device file:
  ls -l /dev/<myDeviceFileName>
<myDeviceFileName> : Device file name
